Pros 

1.open source

2.supports multiple programming languages
java , c#, .net,python perl ruby perl php javascript

3.supports all the platforms/OS
windows, macos, linux , unix

4.Cross browser testing
chrome FF Safari Edge Opera

5.Headless browsers
PhantomJs, HTMLUnitDriver Chrome, Firefox Headless

6.can be integrated with any open source unit testing framework
such as Testng,JUnit -- TDD

7.BDD Frameworks
Cucumber, JBehave and  Serenity

8.Light Weight

9.Available in the form of APIS

10. CI-CD
Jenkins

11.can be executed on local machine , cloud/VM/Servers
BrowserStack SauceLabs AWS Docker

12.Customize webdriver codebase -- source code will be shared

13.Wrappers -- Appium, Protractor, Watir, Robot Framework.


Cons

1.as it is open source, no direct support.

2.you need to learn programming  -- No scriptless or codeless Automation.

3.no desktop app auotmation support.

4.no report for test results.

5.for any extra work: test cases designing, report, build, CI-CD.

6.no bar code and no captcha.



